<section xml:id="C24.S4">
<title>Basic Properties</title>         
<subsection xml:id="C24.S4.SS1">
<title>Difference Equations</title>        
   
<para xml:id="C24.S4.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C24.S4.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="24.4.1" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E1">B_{n}\left(x+1\right)-B_{n}\left(x\right)=nx^{n-1},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.2" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E2">E_{n}\left(x+1\right)+E_{n}\left(x\right)=2x^{n}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C24.S4.SS2">
<title>Symmetry</title>        
   
<para xml:id="C24.S4.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C24.S4.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="24.4.3" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E3">B_{n}\left(1-x\right)=(-1)^{n}B_{n}\left(x\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.4" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E4">E_{n}\left(1-x\right)=(-1)^{n}E_{n}\left(x\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C24.S4.SS2.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="24.4.5" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E5">(-1)^{n}B_{n}\left(-x\right)=B_{n}\left(x\right)+nx^{n-1},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.6" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E6">(-1)^{n+1}E_{n}\left(-x\right)=E_{n}\left(x\right)-2x^{n}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C24.S4.SS3">
<title>Sums of Powers</title>            
<para xml:id="C24.S4.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C24.S4.SS3.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="24.4.7" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E7">\sum_{k=1}^{m}k^{n}=\frac{B_{n+1}\left(m+1\right)-B_{n+1}}{n+1},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.8" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E8">\sum_{k=1}^{m}(-1)^{m-k}k^{n}=\frac{E_{n}\left(m+1\right)+(-1)^{m}E_{n}\left(0 \right)}{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C24.S4.SS3.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="24.4.9" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E9">\sum_{k=0}^{m-1}(a+dk)^{n}={\frac{d^{n}}{n+1}\left(B_{n+1}\left(m+\frac{a}{d} \right)-B_{n+1}\left(\frac{a}{d}\right)\right)},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.10" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E10">\sum_{k=0}^{m-1}(-1)^{k}(a+dk)^{n}={\frac{d^{n}}{2}\left((-1)^{m-1}E_{n}\left( m+\frac{a}{d}\right)+E_{n}\left(\frac{a}{d}\right)\right)}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C24.S4.SS3.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="24.4.11" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E11">\sum_{\begin{subarray}{c}k=1\\ \left(k,m\right)=1\end{subarray}}^{m}k^{n}=\frac{1}{n+1}\sum_{j=1}^{n+1}{n+1 \choose j}\*\left(\prod_{p\mathbin{|}m}(1-p^{n-j})B_{n+1-j}\right)m^{j}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C24.S4.SS4">
<title>Finite Expansions</title>             
<para xml:id="C24.S4.SS4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C24.S4.SS4.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="24.4.12" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E12">B_{n}\left(x+h\right)=\sum_{k=0}^{n}{n\choose k}B_{k}\left(x\right)h^{n-k},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.13" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E13">E_{n}\left(x+h\right)=\sum_{k=0}^{n}{n\choose k}E_{k}\left(x\right)h^{n-k},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.14" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E14">E_{n-1}\left(x\right)=\frac{2}{n}\sum_{k=0}^{n}{n\choose k}(1-2^{k})B_{k}x^{n- k},</Math> <Math equation-number="24.4.15" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E15">B_{2n}=\frac{2n}{2^{2n}(2^{2n}-1)}\sum_{k=0}^{n-1}{2n-1\choose 2k}E_{2k},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.16" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E16">E_{2n}=\frac{1}{2n+1}-\sum_{k=1}^{n}{2n\choose 2k-1}\frac{2^{2k}(2^{2k-1}-1)B_ {2k}}{k},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.17" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E17">E_{2n}=1-\sum_{k=1}^{n}{2n\choose 2k-1}\frac{2^{2k}(2^{2k}-1)B_{2k}}{2k}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C24.S4.SS5">
<title>Multiplication Formulas</title>         
 
<paragraph xml:id="C24.S4.Px1">
<title>Raabe’s Theorem</title>    
<para xml:id="C24.S4.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C24.S4.Px1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="24.4.18" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E18">B_{n}\left(mx\right)=m^{n-1}\sum_{k=0}^{m-1}B_{n}\left(x+\frac{k}{m}\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C24.S4.Px1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C24.S4.Px1.p2.s1">
Next, <Math equation-number="24.4.19" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E19">E_{n}\left(mx\right)=-\frac{2m^{n}}{n+1}\sum_{k=0}^{m-1}(-1)^{k}B_{n+1}\left(x +\frac{k}{m}\right), if m=2,4,6,\dots,</Math> <Math equation-number="24.4.20" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E20">E_{n}\left(mx\right)=m^{n}\sum_{k=0}^{m-1}(-1)^{k}E_{n}\left(x+\frac{k}{m} \right), if m=1,3,5,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C24.S4.Px1.p2.s2">
<Math equation-number="24.4.21" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E21">B_{n}\left(x\right)=2^{n-1}\left(B_{n}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}x\right)+B_{n}\left( \tfrac{1}{2}x+\tfrac{1}{2}\right)\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.22" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E22">E_{n-1}\left(x\right)=\frac{2}{n}\left(B_{n}\left(x\right)-2^{n}B_{n}\left( \tfrac{1}{2}x\right)\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.23" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E23">E_{n-1}\left(x\right)=\frac{2^{n}}{n}\left(B_{n}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}x+\tfrac{1}{ 2}\right)-B_{n}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}x\right)\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="24.4.24" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E24">B_{n}\left(mx\right)=m^{n}B_{n}\left(x\right)+n\sum_{k=1}^{n}\sum_{j=0}^{k-1}( -1)^{j}{n\choose k}\*\left(\sum_{r=1}^{m-1}\frac{e^{2\pi i(k-j)r/m}}{(1-e^{2 \pi ir/m})^{n}}\right)(j+mx)^{n-1}, if n=1,2,\dots, m=2,3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</paragraph>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C24.S4.SS6">
<title>Special Values</title>        
  
 
<para xml:id="C24.S4.SS6.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C24.S4.SS6.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="24.4.25" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E25">B_{n}\left(0\right)=(-1)^{n}B_{n}\left(1\right)=B_{n}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C24.S4.SS6.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="24.4.26" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E26">E_{n}\left(0\right)=-E_{n}\left(1\right)=-\frac{2}{n+1}(2^{n+1}-1)B_{n+1}, if n&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="13" xml:id="C24.S4.SS6.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="24.4.27" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E27">B_{n}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\right)=-(1-2^{1-n})B_{n},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.28" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E28">E_{n}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\right)=2^{-n}E_{n}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="14" xml:id="C24.S4.SS6.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="24.4.29" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E29">B_{2n}\left(\tfrac{1}{3}\right)=B_{2n}\left(\tfrac{2}{3}\right)=-\tfrac{1}{2}( 1-3^{1-2n})B_{2n}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="15" xml:id="C24.S4.SS6.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="24.4.30" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E30">E_{2n-1}\left(\tfrac{1}{3}\right)=-E_{2n-1}\left(\tfrac{2}{3}\right)=-\frac{(1 -3^{1-2n})(2^{2n}-1)}{2n}B_{2n}, if n=1,2,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="16" xml:id="C24.S4.SS6.p1.s6">
<Math equation-number="24.4.31" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E31">B_{n}\left(\tfrac{1}{4}\right)=(-1)^{n}B_{n}\left(\tfrac{3}{4}\right)=-\frac{1 -2^{1-n}}{2^{n}}B_{n}-\frac{n}{4^{n}}E_{n-1}, if n=1,2,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="7" sentence-num-in-section="17" xml:id="C24.S4.SS6.p1.s7">
<Math equation-number="24.4.32" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E32">B_{2n}\left(\tfrac{1}{6}\right)=B_{2n}\left(\tfrac{5}{6}\right)=\tfrac{1}{2}(1 -2^{1-2n})(1-3^{1-2n})B_{2n},</Math> <Math equation-number="24.4.33" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E33">E_{2n}\left(\tfrac{1}{6}\right)=E_{2n}\left(\tfrac{5}{6}\right)=\frac{1+3^{-2n }}{2^{2n+1}}E_{2n}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C24.S4.SS7">
<title>Derivatives</title>        
 
<para xml:id="C24.S4.SS7.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="18" xml:id="C24.S4.SS7.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="24.4.34" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E34">\frac{\mathrm{d}}{\mathrm{d}x}B_{n}\left(x\right)=nB_{n-1}\left(x\right), if n=1,2,\dots,</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.35" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E35">\frac{\mathrm{d}}{\mathrm{d}x}E_{n}\left(x\right)=nE_{n-1}\left(x\right), if n=1,2,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C24.S4.SS8">
<title>Symbolic Operations</title>        
   
<para xml:id="C24.S4.SS8.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="19" xml:id="C24.S4.SS8.p1.s1">
Let <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S4.SS8.p1.m1">P(x)</Math> denote any polynomial in <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S4.SS8.p1.m2">x</Math> , and after expanding set <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S4.SS8.p1.m3">(B(x))^{n}=B_{n}\left(x\right)</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S4.SS8.p1.m4">(E(x))^{n}=E_{n}\left(x\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="20" xml:id="C24.S4.SS8.p1.s2">
Then <Math equation-number="24.4.36" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E36">P(B(x)+1)-P(B(x))=P^{\prime}(x),</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.37" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E37">B_{n}\left(x+h\right)=(B(x)+h)^{n},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.38" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E38">P(E(x)+1)+P(E(x))=2P(x),</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.4.39" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S4.E39">E_{n}\left(x+h\right)=(E(x)+h)^{n}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="21" xml:id="C24.S4.SS8.p1.s3">
For these results and also connections with the umbral calculus seeGessel (2003).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C24.S4.SS9">
<title>Relations to Other Functions</title>        
   
 
 
<para xml:id="C24.S4.SS9.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="22" xml:id="C24.S4.SS9.p1.s1">
For the relation of Bernoulli numbers to the Riemann zeta function see §25.6, and to the Eulerian numbers see (26.14.11).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
